assets.name: #07941 - FULL SEND METACARD
assets.description:
Explore FULL SEND METACARD.

Built on the Ethereum blockchain with a limited supply of 10,000 NFTs, the FULL SEND METACARD will give exclusive access to what FULL SEND does in the physical world and metaverse.

As a company, the FULL SEND goal is to launch more FULL SEND branded ventures, which include lounges, gyms, festivals, casinos, restaurants and more. FULL SEND is going international.

In addition, we will take these same ventures of products and physical locations and will launch them in the metaverse. This will include FULL SEND apparel, virtual stores, virtual festivals, metaverse casinos, and FULL SEND NFT recording artists. This list will continue to grow.

Owning a FULL SEND METACARD allows you to get in early on what is the beginning of a long journey for the FULL SEND brand.

assets.name: Coullet #75
assets.description:
The Coullet attractor emerges from a system presented by P. Coullet et al. in 1979 that describes the evolution of a damped, harmonic pendulum driven by an external force. The system belongs to the broader family of memory oscillators.

This system is part of Strange Attractors -- an interactive generative art project that simulates multi-dimensional, chaotic systems and visualizes their evolution as an SVG using nothing but an Ethereum smart contract.
by @cxkoda

For more information visit https://strangeattractors.art.

assets.name: Waterfront #14, by JeaN Baskeeait
assets.description:
Painting by JeaN Baskeeait 

The middle of five siblings living in a crammed apartment, quiet boy Jean would escape to Brooklyn Bridge to gaze at the city views. At night he’d see himself to sleep picturing the recent mood of the city and holding onto the vision of the skyline. Fascinated to discover more, Jean began traveling across cities, supporting himself with menial jobs. Unable to afford a camera and with a deep desire to capture the emotions he’d take in from the views, Jean started to sketch and paint. Today Jean spends a large part of the year travelling to seek out new inspiration. Whilst when in his studio back home, he isn’t afraid to use oil to contrast light and haze in his paintings.
